Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of directed acyclic graphs (DAGs) to model causal theories and estimate parameters from observational data. This is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well as in statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to determine equivalence between causal models, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the extraction of causal structures from empirical data, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
